<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/92.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">White</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-09"><hi rend="italic">August 9,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee instructs Mr. White to send the department a copy of the note
                            from the French Government accepting invitation to join the opium
                            commission as outlined in his telegram of July 10.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>